## interrupts-extended

**Value type:** `<phandle> <prop-encoded-array>`

The *interrupts-extended* property lists the interrupt(s) generated by a device. *interrupts-extended* should be used instead of *interrupts* when a device is connected to multiple interrupt controllers as it encodes a parent phandle with each interrupt specifier.

The *interrupts* and *interrupts-extended* properties are mutually exclusive. A device node should use one or the other, but not both. If both are present, *interrupts-extended* takes precedence.

```dts
/* arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun50i-h6.dtsi */
mmc0: mmc@4020000 {
    interrupts-extended = <&gic GIC_SPI 35 IRQ_TYPE_LEVEL_HIGH>,
                          <&r_intc 6 IRQ_TYPE_LEVEL_HIGH>;
};

/* pic uses #interrupt-cells=<2>, gic uses #interrupt-cells=<1> */
device {
    interrupts-extended = <&pic 0xA 8>, <&gic 0xda>;
};
```
